{"title":"Gallery: A classic crescendo at the 2021 Milan-San Remo","link":"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/gallery-a-classic-crescendo-at-the-2021-milan-san-remo/","date":1616374673000,"content":"<p>In many ways it was your typical Milan-San Remo. There was the usual slow burn over many hours, the frenzied jostling for position ahead of the Cipressa, and a short blast of explosive action on the Poggio. But it didn&#8217;t end the way we expected.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It wasn&#8217;t the Poggio that proved most decisive; nor did we get the reduced bunch sprint that seemed likely with a kilometre to go. Rather it was a late attack from Jasper Stuyven that ended up staying away, leading to the biggest result of the Belgian&#8217;s career.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Photographers Kristof Ramon and Cor Vos were there to capture all the action and you can see their handiwork in the gallery that follows. And if you haven&#8217;t already, be sure to check out Cosmo Catalano&#8217;s <a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/how-the-race-was-won-milano-sanremo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">How the Race Was Won</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"921\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-4-1340x921.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504782\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-4.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=504782\" class=\"wp-image-504782\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-4-1340x921.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-4-650x447.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-4-190x131.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-4-1080x743.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-4-16x11.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-4.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Mathieu van der Poel (Alpecin-Fenix) cut an arresting figure at the teams presentation.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-5-1340x893.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504783\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-5.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=504783\" class=\"wp-image-504783\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-5-1340x893.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-5-650x433.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-5-190x127.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-5-1080x720.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-5-16x11.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-5.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">In his 17th tilt at Milan-San Remo, Philippe Gilbert (Lotto-Soudal) was hoping to win the only Monument not on his palmares.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"870\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-6-1340x870.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504786\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-6.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=504786\" class=\"wp-image-504786\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-6-1340x870.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-6-650x422.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-6-190x123.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-6-1080x701.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-6-16x10.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-6.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Rolling out of Milan &#8230;</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-7-1340x893.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504789\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-7.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=504789\" class=\"wp-image-504789\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-7-1340x893.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-7-650x433.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-7-190x127.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-7-1080x720.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-7-16x11.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-7.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">&#8230; with tram tracks forcing some early concentration.</figcaption></figure></li><li 