lery-item__caption\">&#8230; but a handful of riders were able to battle across, ensuring the Frenchman wouldn&#8217;t get away. Note Caleb Ewan (Lotto-Soudal) in the background, looking the strongest he ever has on the Poggio.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-7-1340x893.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504891\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-7.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=504891\" class=\"wp-image-504891\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-7-1340x893.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-7-650x433.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-7-190x127.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-7-1080x720.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-7-16x11.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-7.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Down off the Poggio, the race seemed destined for a sprint but Stuyven had other ideas. He punched away with about 2.5 km to go and soon had Soren Kragh Andersen (DSM) for company. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-5-1340x893.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504888\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-5.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=504888\" class=\"wp-image-504888\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-5-1340x893.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-5-650x433.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-5-190x127.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-5-1080x720.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-5-16x11.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-5.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The late move looked certain to be caught, but Stuyven somehow managed to hold on &#8230;</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-33-1340x893.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504852\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-33.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=504852\" class=\"wp-image-504852\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-33-1340x893.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-33-650x433.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-33-190x127.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-33-1080x720.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-33-16x11.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-33.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">&#8230; taking an unexpected victory ahead of Ewan and Van Aert. Sagan finished fast to take fourth.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-3-1340x893.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504884\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-3.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=504884\" class=\"wp-image-504884\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-3-1340x893.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-3-650x433.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-3-190x127.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-3-1080x720.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-3-16x11.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-corvos-3.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"941\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-35-1340x941.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504857\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-35.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=504857\" class=\"wp-image-504857\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-35-1340x941.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-35-650x457.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-35-190x133.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-35-1080x759.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-35-16x11.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-35.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The UCI&#8217;s &#8216;no hugging&#8217; rule be damned.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-40-1340x893.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504869\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-40.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=504869\" class=\"wp-image-504869\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-40-1340x893.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-40-650x433.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-40-190x127.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-40-1080x720.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-40-16x11.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-40.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">If Ewan&#8217;s second place in 2018 (behind a solo Vincenzo Nibali) didn&#8217;t already prove he can win Milan-San Remo, this year&#8217;s edition <a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/ewan-after-san-remo-that-confirmed-that-i-could-potentially-win-the-race-one-day/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">certainly did</a>. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-42-1340x893.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504873\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-42.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=504873\" class=\"wp-image-504873\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-42-1340x893.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-42-650x433.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-42-190x127.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-42-1080x720.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-42-16x11.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-42.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Trek-Segafredo ended up having a stellar weekend. They didn&#8217;t just win Milan-San Remo: <a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/elisa-longo-borghini-wins-trofeo-alfredo-binda/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Elisa Longo Borghini also won Trofeo Alfredo Binda</a> and Matteo Moschetti also won the smaller Per Sempre &#8220;Alfredo&#8221;.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-43-1340x893.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504875\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-43.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=504875\" class=\"wp-image-504875\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-43-1340x893.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-43-650x433.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-43-190x127.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-43-1080x720.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-43-16x11.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2021-milan-sanremo-kramon-43.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Jasper Stuyven, <a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/jasper-stuyven-wins-milano-san-remo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">winner of the 2021 Milan-San Remo</a>.</figcaption></figure></li></ul></figure>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/gallery-a-classic-crescendo-at-the-2021-milan-san-remo/\">Gallery: A classic crescendo at the 2021 Milan-San Remo</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://cyclingtips.com\">CyclingTips</a>.</p>","author":"Matt de Neef","siteTitle":"CyclingTips","siteHash":"30feca30fb3902119bf2da6559e7337232527b61c9abe0a00f5d7543c6aa6c84","entryHash":"d11e60bc5c336cc4168c1afdbe5eb5078f3ffdc3b56cfcc534df7b371269e05d","category":"Cycling"}